
{center}
{subhead} Games from Alive Mediasoft Ltd.{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

We've got some information on a couple of new games from Alive Mediasoft,
Phoenix Fighters and The Prophet.
{p} {p}
PRESS RELEASE FROM ALIVE MEDIASOFT LTD
{p} {p}
APRIL 11TH 1999
{p} {p}
*Phoenix Fighters* *£14.99*
{p} {p}
Release Date - End of May '99
{p} {p}
GAME FEATURES
{p} {p}
- Many different kinds of gameplay:{p}
  One Player Missions:{p}
    Good variation of themes and objectives. Tricky in-game hint messages
    giving a good exercise for your braincells. Hidden bonus objects to
    be found. Missions are played with the cash and equipments from your
    last mission. Password given on every third mission.{p}
  Two Player Missions:{p}
    Missions as above but requires two cooperating players. Teamwork
    at its best!{p}
  Gate Races:{p}
    Fly the race-track in the shortest time possible, passing all gates
    in order. Three difficulties. Fight for at place in the hall of fame
    (one player mode) or to beat your opponent (two player mode).
  Gem Races:{p}
    Race as above, but the aim is to collect all gems a quick as possible.
  Dog Fight:{p}
    The mode that really test your skills. Fight against your friend to be
    the one that last longest. Survival of the fittest are true indeed, so
    plan your choice of ships, weapons and equipments well, and go for the
    valuable gems to gain cash. Also, a bit of luck is not bad thing, if
    you are unlucky, a single well aimed shot could damage your ship so
    severly that you will be glad if you make it back to the base for
    repairments. The Dog Fight mode is configurable in aspects of starting
    cash, number of ships and more.
{p} {p}
- Around 200 levels divided up on:{p}
    80 one player missions{p}
    50 two player missions{p}
    20 gate races{p}
    20 gem races{p}
    40 dog fight levels
{p} {p}
- Fast action, constantly at 50 frames per second, even on low-end cpu's{p}
- Large Levels, 512*800 pixels{p}
- More than 128 colours onscreen{p}
- Complex priority based and distance controlled volume sound system{p}
- Upgrade your ship. Dock your ship at your base at any time to buy,
  sell and repair weapons, equipments and ships{p}
- 20 different ships to use, all with individual characteristics{p}
- 15 weapons to choose from, including high explosive weapons. Watch out
  for the shockwaves!{p}
- Realistic collisions, giving your ship a bounce and spin{p}
- Doors, some opening for a specific player, one-way doors, force field
  doors and more{p}
- Teleporters, for quick transfer between different places in the level{p}
- Walls which you can blast your way through.{p}
- Virus, obstacles growing and growing in size until you destroy its source{p}
- Extra goodies to pick up. Gems (cash), fuel, shields, extra lives...{p}
- Enemies with individual energy shields and weapons{p}
- Special walls, reflecting shots that hits it{p]
- Buttons to hit to activate doors, redirect teleporters and blow up new
  paths in the level{p}
- Race record file, saving name and time for the five fastest racers on each
  difficulty for each race level{p}
- Force fields, tricky obstacles in the mission levels, learn to take
  advantage of them in the races!{p}
- Coward detection system, punishing any player in dog fights which tries
  too defensive tactics!{p}
- Power Unit Attachment, connecting your ship with a power unit adds another
  dimension to the ship controls. Mainly used in missions.
{p} {p}
HARDWARE REQUIREMENTS
{p} {p}
Platform:           Amiga. PAL display mode{p}
CPU:                68000+ (68020+ for some improvements){p}
OS Version:         1.2+ (v33+){p}
Graphics Chipset:   OCS+{p}
Memory:             0.5MB Chipmem + another 0.5MB of any memory type
{p} {p}
---------------------------------------------------
{p} {p}
*The Prophet * *£19.99*
{p} {p}
Release Data: April 19th
{p} {p}
Feature List
{p} {p}
Over 200,00 locations set in the city, dungeons, graveyard, ctypt, temple
and an alternate dimension.
{p} {p}
More than 50 different types of locations, including shops, tavers, guilds,
spinners, false walls, Teleports, buttons, levers, ect.
{p} {p}
Every monster tha two different attack moves also graphics when defending,
hurt and dying. A total of 25 frames of animation for each monster.
{p} {p}
Each type of monster has totally unique strenghs and weaknesses, some have
poison, disease or magic attack. Some may try to weaken you by attacking you
arms or legs, others might beat you unconscious.
{p} {p}
Four different styles of attack that vary in efficiency depending on the
weapon used and your skill in that attack. A defensive move, as well as a
run away for mummy`s boys.
{p} {p}
Dozens of different items, including keys, foods, potions and spells. Each
weapon has its own individual statistics so you can see how good it is for
hacking, slashing, jabbing, defending as well as how heavy it is and how
easy to use.
{p} {p}
Complex and realistic character health, with overall health (HP), as well as
individual body areas. All health effects fully displayed on your character,
so you can see just by looking how bad the woun d on his arm really is. Many
different types of poison and disease that can spread through your body, all
displayed in full colour.
{p} {p}
A full graphical display of your character showing the different armour worn
and weapons held.
{p} {p}
No fixed route through the game, Go where you want, do what you want, when
you want too. Discover plots within plots, help poor unfortunates or just
kill for money and power. Quests that change the shape of the game,
completing one may open or close another. Will the city`s inhabitants sing
of your deeds, or fearfully whisper your name.
{p} {p}
A unique learning system, that means you choose how your character will
advance. Train in magic, thievery, medicine or figting skills.
{p} {p}
HARDWARE REQUIREMENTS
{p} {p}
All Amigas with Hard Drive or CD-Rom